title: Asylum requests; from 1980
maintainer_displayname: ZBO | Centraal Bureau voor de Statistiek
name: asylum-requests-from-1980
notes:
Requests for asylum by citizenship of the asylum seeker. The data refer to asylum requests by persons of all ages. 
Citizenships with at least 50 (first) asylum applications within a year are included separately. Apart from the total number of requests the number of first requests and subsequent requests is also included. This distinction between first requests and subsequent requests could not be made before the reference year 2007. For some individual countries, no data is available for the years before 1994. However, the numbers of requests for asylum for these countries are included in the total number of requests. In all cases it concerns small numbers.

Data available from: 1980.

Status of the figures: The asylum figures for 2012 and further are still provisional. The asylum figures from 2014 are defined slightly different than the figures for previous years. Family members, who have arrived within three months after an asylum seeker has received a residence permit (4 thousand in 2014), are no longer counted as asylum seekers. The figures in the table are rounded to fives. As a consequence, some subtotals do not add up to the totals. 

Changes as of 28 January 2015:
The (provisional) figures for 2014 have been added. 
                                                               
When will new figures be published?
New figures will be published February 2016.
